body: This PR pushes forward the DHT implementation in various ways, in particular by implementing packet handling for the Nodes and Ping services. The use of MonadRandom is replaced for all cryptographic purposes by a new monad class MonadRandomBytes, which is used as a wrapper around System.Entropy to obtain system-provided secure randomness. There is no actual networking implemented yet, but some more of the architecture is in place. Some of that architecture is designed also to support a network simulator which I'm working on in my branch simNet, but this PR does not include that simulator. I've tried to make the parts of the spec which this PR implements readable and complete, and explicitly noted the few places where I haven't precisely copied c-toxcore's behaviour. This PR also fixes #125. I can have a go at splitting the PR up into smaller chunks if that would be helpful, but the high degree of interdependency between the changes would make this difficult. Criticism of code and design welcomed. --- This change isâ€‚[](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/hs-toxcore/126)

comment_regular_data.body: This PR isn't happy with the changes in Operation.lhs. Can you merge master into it? Also, can you enable the checkbox that lets me push to your branch?
Rebased to latest master, and checked the box.

So the system is saying I should write more tests. It's right, of course. I've been putting it off because I'm not sure how best to go about testing these things, but I suppose it should be done before merge really. Let me think about it.
Also, this code seems to be unhappy with lenses-0.1.7. Perhaps set an upper limit for the version we can use?

commit.message: fleshed out Time module, using System.Clock for monotonic time
check if already in lists before sending node request in handleNodesResponse
separate TimedT to its own module (to avoid import loops)

'"ping" -> "check" for the once-per-60s Nodes Requests

to prevent confusion with ping packets
don't accept multiple replies to a request

Mark DHT.Operation as Trustworthy rather than Safe

(this got lost in the rebase somewhere...)
remove superfluous functions DhtRequestPacket.encrypt and encode
use lens-family package in place of lenses
fix mistakes in spec for Ping Response handling
